1
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:13,050
What do you want?

2
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:14,760
Stay back!

3
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:16,800
Don't come over.

4
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,280
Don't touch me.

5
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:20,940
Don't touch me.

6
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:23,200
Don't touch me.

7
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,840
Help! Someone help me!

8
00:00:27,320 --> 00:00:28,200
Don't touch me.

9
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:29,320
Stay away.

10
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:31,720
Don't!

11
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:23,000
Meow.

12
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,610
Hello, Mr. Wang.

13
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,600
Yes, yes.

14
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,460
The company has a minor issue.

15
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,520
Don't worry, we'll handle it.

16
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,960
Sorry. Okay.

17
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:26,360
Mr. Chen.

18
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,920
The business reps from those companies are here.

19
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:31,000
They brought lawyers demanding compensation. What do we do?

20
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,920
Do you know

21
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,200
how to do your job?

22
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,520
Tell them I'm not here.

23
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,800
I already told them.

24
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,530
They said they'll wait for you.

25
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,400
Which one do you like? It's yours.

26
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,160
Really?

27
00:02:59,160 --> 00:02:59,920
Really.

28
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,520
I'll take this one.

29
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,320
Sure.

30
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,000
Your husband and that Strawberry Meow Meow

31
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,400
are both down and out now.

32
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,880
What do you plan to do?

33
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,890
Kick them while they're down and go for broke?

34
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:14,680
What else?

35
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,300
They wanted to destroy me.

36
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,760
Have you heard the old saying,

37
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,079
'Don't drive a dog into a corner,

38
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,600
or it will bite you'?

39
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,079
You mean you want me to let them go?

40
00:03:27,079 --> 00:03:28,610
I want you to free yourself.

41
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,820
If you're obsessed with revenge,

42
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,540
you'll lose yourself.

43
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,920
I actually feel

44
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,880
I just found myself.

45
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:44,180
Did you really find yourself?

46
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,720
What does the real you want?

47
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,500
Have you thought about it?

48
00:03:49,079 --> 00:03:50,480
When you first came to me,

49
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,079
you wanted me to save your husband and child.

50
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:54,600
But now that they're saved,

51
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,920
you can plan your future life.

52
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,200
My future life?

53
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,320
Say goodbye to the past,

54
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,680
bring Xixi to live with you,

55
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,120
and live a good life.

56
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,640
For now, I might still need

57
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,600
Shili to look after Xixi.

58
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,940
At a time like this,

59
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:19,320
whether the child is at home or at his grandmother's,

60
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,450
I won't feel at ease.

61
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,400
Indeed.

62
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,360
Okay, you can rest assured about this.

63
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:49,960
You...

64
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,360
Why are you wearing my clothes?

65
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,850
What are you doing here?

66
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:55,800
How are...

67
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,680
Jian.

68
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,720
Every time I start a new live streaming room,

69
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,560
it gets banned immediately.

70
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,080
I have no source of income anymore.

71
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,780
You have to be responsible for me.

72
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,800
Responsible for you?

73
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,120
Who is responsible for me?

74
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,000
If it weren't for you,

75
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,760
would I have ended up like this?

76
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:25,360
If it weren't for you,

77
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,040
my family of three

78
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:28,300
would still be living happily together.

79
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,520
Get this straight.

80
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:34,450
Could your company have lasted that long without me?

81
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,800
Think about it.

82
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,480
To cover those previous losses.

83
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:39,880
You...

84
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:52,240
Jian, actually, you don't need to be angry.

85
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,560
We still have a way out.

86
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,520
What way?

87
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,280
Did you forget?

88
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,200
Your wife still has a

89
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,500
huge accident insurance policy.

90
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,080
Hello, Mom.

91
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,720
Hospital? I...

92
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,560
I'm coming to pick you up right now.

93
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,480
Don't worry.

94
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:28,200
I'm waiting to fly away with you.

95
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,500
Once you get the insurance money.

96
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,050
Is it okay not to answer?

97
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,220
I checked the message.

98
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,600
His mom broke her leg.

99
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,060
She's in the hospital.

100
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,000
I've been a free nanny for so many years.

101
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,159
I want to take a day off today.

102
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,040
Fair enough.

103
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,360
But with your mother-in-law's temper,

104
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,080
she'll definitely make a huge scene if you go back.

105
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,940
You might as well just not go back.

106
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,680
That's not what I meant.

107
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,280
I didn't say

108
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,360
I was taking you home or anything.

109
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,690
You can get a hotel room.

110
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:57,920
I mean you go alone and get your own room.

111
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,920
I'm leaving. I'm not going.

112
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,620
I really didn't mean that.

113
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,050
Then why did you bring me here so late at night?

114
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,720
I'm teasing you.

115
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,200
I know you're a good person.

116
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,360
Actually, it's because...

117
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,620
I watched the moon here

118
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:31,960
with you from 12 days in the future.

119
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:35,720
You seemed really relaxed back then.

120
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,960
So I wanted to bring you here.

121
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,880
Yeah.

122
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,159
It really is relaxing.

123
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,820
I don't have to think about anything.

124
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,800
Flowers bloom.

125
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,720
Baby be good.

126
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
No matter how dark

127
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,860
the night gets,

128
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,440
I'm here.

129
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,420
It's getting late.

130
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:27,760
I'll call a cab and take you home.

131
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,520
Okay.

132
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,440
Come on, get up.

133
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,920
Be careful.

134
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,760
You didn't forget the lantern, did you?

135
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,280
You go up first.

136
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,720
In case the driver can't reach you.

137
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:50,560
Alright.

138
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:54,000
Help! Someone save me!

139
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:55,720
Chen Jian.

140
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,290
Put down the dagger.

141
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:58,640
Don't.

142
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,280
It's my voice.

143
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,880
Wenxin. What happened to you?

144
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,280
Wenxin, can you hear me?

145
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:17,760
Wenxin, did something happen to you?

146
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,520
Wenxin, say something.

147
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:28,280
It seems

148
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,480
the price for changing fate

149
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
hasn't stopped.

150
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,960
Sun Wen has done enough for me.

151
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,090
I can't let him take risks with me anymore.

152
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,200
Wenxin.

153
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,160
What's wrong?

154
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,800
Nothing. Why are you here?

155
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,200
I saw the lights were out, and you hadn't come over.

156
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,120
I'm fine.

157
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:51,120
I'll be okay.

158
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,720
What could happen to me?

159
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:57,600
Sir,

160
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,610
you've arrived, right?

161
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,680
Okay, great. Coming.

162
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,480
Let's go.
